intro: The Joe Burton Award was awarded annually to the Central Hockey League's (CHL) scoring champion. The award was named after the CHL's career point leader, Joe Burton, who accumulated 985 points in 11 seasons with the Oklahoma City Blazerss. The award was named after Burton starting in the 2003-04 season.
